contentrichtext.text: {{Infobox protected area of Australia | name = Kwiambal National Park | iucn_category = II | image = MacIntyre Falls.JPG | caption = MacIntyre Falls | map = | map_caption = | locator_x = | locator_y = | location = | nearest_town_or_city= [[Ashford, New South Wales|Ashford]] | coordinates = {{Coord|29|09|15|S|150|59|02|E|type:landmark_region:AU-NSW|display=inline,title}} | area = | established = 2000 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | managing_authorities = [[National Parks and Wildlife Service (New South Wales)|NSW National Parks and Wildlife Service]] | official_site = http://www.nationalparks.nsw.gov.au }} '''Kwiambal''' is a national park in [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]] located about 30 km from the town of [[Ashford, New South Wales|Ashford]]. The [[Severn River (New South Wales)|Severn River]] and [[Macintyre River]], both flow through and finally converge in the park below the MacIntyre falls. The park is studded with [[granite]] outcrops and also features the [[Ashford Caves]].<ref>[http://www.nationalparks.nsw.gov.au/parks.nsf/parkContent/N0156?OpenDocument&ParkKey=N0156&Type=Xo Kwiambal National Park]</ref> ==References== {{Reflist}} ==See also== * [[Protected areas of New South Wales]] {{National Parks of New South Wales}} [[Category:National parks of New South Wales]] [[Category:2000 establishments in Australia]] {{NewSouthWales-protected-area-stub}}
